<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="738" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A Pacific War/218:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-13">August 13, 1942</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                    August 13—4:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3736. American interests—Philippines. Legation’s 3686, August
                                    10.<note n="97" xml:id="d738fn97">Not printed; it reported that
                                    International Red Cross efforts to send a delegation to the
                                    Philippines had failed (740.00115A Pacific War/213).</note>
                                Intercroixrouge states Japanese authorities gave following
                                information to Intercroixrouge’s representative Tokyo regarding
                                Philippines: “Prisoners of war and civilian internees under good
                                conditions. Internment camp Santo Tomas, Manila, large and well
                                organized. Sanitary, food and clothing situation prisoners and
                                internees good.”</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>